-- Nigeria to Adopt Mining Chemicals to Curb Bombings, Punch Says
-- B y   V i n c e n t   N w a n m a
-- 2012-03-04T08:24:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-04/nigeria-to-adopt-mining-chemicals-to-curb-bombings-punch-says.html
     Mar. 4 (Bloomberg)-- The Nigerian government is planning to
replace the explosives used in the  mining industry  with chemical
explosives, to curb the spate of bombings by Islamic sect, Boko
Haram, Punch  reported , citing Musa Sada, Minister of Mines and
Steel Development.  The government is supporting a local company to go into
partnership with a Chinese firm to produce the chemical
explosives, the Lagos-based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Vincent Nwanma in Lagos at 
 vnwanma@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dulue Mbachu at 
 dmbachu@bloomberg.net  